marked: In the present study, using a VBM analysis across the whole brain, we firstly identified positive correlations between the GMV and the DB score in the right anterior superior temporal gyrus (STG), the right posterior STG, the left IFG and the left Rolandic operculum.
324 right-handed healthy young adults participated in this study.
The working-memory capacity was measured by the DB subtest of the digit span test in the Chinese Revised Wechsler Adult Intelligence Scale (WAIS-RC)
However, the VBM analysis revealed that the DB scores were positively correlated with the GMVs in four clusters
was located in the right posterior STG
a counterpart of the putative Wernicke’s area in the left hemisphere.
cated in the left IFG, corresponding to the putative Broca’s area
The four seed regions (ROIs) where the GMVs were positively correlated with the DB scores were selected for the rsFC analysis.
the DB scores were negatively correlated with the rsFC between ROI 2 (the right posterior STG) and the left insula
